Today's experiment

45
00:06:20,007 --> 00:06:25,001
uses a clear super-ball.

46
00:06:25,001 --> 00:06:30,002
We put the ball into a round glass of water.

47
00:06:30,002 --> 00:06:32,005
If we do this what will happen?

48
00:06:35,005 --> 00:06:37,007
It looks much bigger.

49
00:06:37,007 --> 00:06:41,002
The glass is acting like a lens.

50
00:06:44,003 --> 00:06:49,007
Now, this time...

51
00:06:52,009 --> 00:06:55,008
we put a small sticker on the ball.

52
00:07:01,004 --> 00:07:05,001
When we look at this from behind...

53
00:07:07,005 --> 00:07:10,007
It looks big.

54
00:07:10,007 --> 00:07:14,003
Now this is the problem.

55
00:07:14,003 --> 00:07:18,002
We put the ball in the water like this.

56
00:07:18,003 --> 00:07:21,007
If we do the way we see the sticker

57
00:07:21,008 --> 00:07:25,004
How will it change?

58
00:07:36,008 --> 00:07:40,001
Well then let's try it.

59
00:07:43,008 --> 00:07:46,004
We'll present the answer at the end of the program.

60
