65
00:09:02,001 --> 00:09:06,009
Now, let's try it for real.

66
00:09:06,009 --> 00:09:11,000
What will happen, please look carefully, won't you?

67
00:09:16,008 --> 00:09:21,001
Did you get it? The answer is...

68
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:29,005
Even though the ball looks bigger...

69
00:09:29,005 --> 00:09:34,005
the sticker looks smaller.

70
00:09:34,006 --> 00:09:37,001
Why do you think that is?

71
00:09:37,002 --> 00:09:42,005
Well at first the sticker looked big because the light was bent.

72
00:09:42,005 --> 00:09:46,003
Light has a property so that when it travels between different materials...

73
00:09:46,003 --> 00:09:48,004
At that boundary the light is bent.

74
00:09:48,004 --> 00:09:50,004
And the ball in the water...

75
00:09:50,004 --> 00:09:54,000
From here on we think for ourselves.

76
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,000
From here on everyone is a thinking crow.


